&lt;h3&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Automotive Detailer&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; San Francisco, CA (Onsite)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;$30-$32 per Hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ever&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Ever, we&#39;re transforming the way people buy electric vehicles by delivering a premium customer experience from start to finish. Every vehicle that reaches our showroom or customer has gone through a meticulous inspection and reconditioning process. As an Automotive Detailer, you&#39;ll play a critical role in ensuring every vehicle looks its absolute best before it reaches its next owner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an experienced Automotive Detailer who takes pride in producing showroom-quality vehicles. This role is responsible for cleaning, restoring, and preparing vehicles throughout the reconditioning process while maintaining Ever&#39;s high cosmetic standards. The ideal candidate has professional detailing experience, excellent attention to detail, and thrives in a fast-paced production environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform complete interior and exterior vehicle detailing to showroom standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wash, dry, clay bar, polish, wax, and apply protective coatings when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vacuum, shampoo carpets, clean upholstery, condition leather, and sanitize interiors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clean windows, mirrors, door jambs, wheels, wheel wells, and engine compartments as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove light stains, water spots, adhesive residue, and minor cosmetic imperfections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate buffers, polishers, extractors, steam cleaners, pressure washers, and other detailing equipment safely and effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspect vehicles before and after detailing to ensure Ever&#39;s quality standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify cosmetic issues requiring additional repair or paint correction and communicate findings to the recon team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare vehicles for photography, showroom display, customer delivery, and transport.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailing equipment and ensure chemicals, tools, and supplies are properly stored and maintained.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep work areas clean, organized, and compliant with company safety standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support vehicle movement and other reconditioning activities as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently meet daily production, quality, and turnaround goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all company safety procedures and maintain a clean, professional work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–5 years of professional automotive detailing experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience detailing a high volume of vehicles in a dealership, reconditioning center, fleet, or automotive environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of automotive detailing chemicals, products, equipment, and industry best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating buffers, polishers, extractors, pressure washers, steam cleaners, and other detailing equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to identify cosmetic defects and recommend appropriate corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail with a commitment to delivering high-quality work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently while collaborating effectively with the Operations team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Valid driver&#39;s license with a clean driving record.&lt;/li&gt;
