&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role:&lt;/strong&gt; Front Desk Receptionist&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; On-site (Costa Mesa, CA)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $17 - $24/ hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ever&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ever is building the future of auto retail. As the first AI-native auto retail platform, we are building the next $100B+ automotive business, starting with electric vehicles. Our AI-native product and operations power our full-stack auto retail business, serving EV buyers and sellers across the nation, both online and offline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based out of San Francisco and expanding nationwide, we are backed by leading investors and led by former tech &amp;amp; automotive professionals from Uber, Tesla, Rivian, Lithia, Penske, Carvana, Lyft, Meta, J.P. Morgan, BCG, and more. After our recently completed Series A financing, we have raised $100M in total equity and debt funding. We are growing rapidly and actively recruiting exceptional talent to join our mission of building the next-generation auto retail platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Greet and check in scheduled guests upon arrival for their appointment slots&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with assigned EV Consultants for seamless handoff for sales consultations and delivery pickups&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure every guest receives a welcoming, professional, and efficient first impression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and maintain the daily schedule for test drives and vehicle deliveries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor showroom traffic and proactively communicate with the sales team to minimize wait times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirm appointments and communicate any delays or changes in real time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate final vehicle key hand-offs during delivery appointments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect guest feedback on their delivery experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate customers on post-sale support via &lt;strong&gt;support@evercars.com&lt;/strong&gt;, including 90-day warranty processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set clear expectations for follow-up communications and review requests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively follow up with recent buyers to encourage positive reviews on Google, Yelp, and other platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean, organized, and professional front desk and lobby environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the “Coffee Zone” is stocked, clean, and welcoming for guests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Answer and route incoming calls, emails, and inquiries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately track customer visits, appointments, and handoffs in internal systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support sales and operations teams with administrative tasks (data entry, paperwork, filing)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Fit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in a front desk, receptionist, retail, or customer-facing role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills with a customer-first mindset&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with the ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable, detail-oriented, and punctual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate with ownership and minimal supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Google Workspace (Docs, Sheets, Calendar)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using CRM or scheduling tools is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable using Slack or similar communication tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
