&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Irvine, CA (Onsite)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead Automotive Detailer&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;$32 - $34 per Hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ever&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Ever, we&#39;re transforming the way people buy electric vehicles by delivering a premium customer experience from start to finish. Every vehicle that reaches our showroom or customer has gone through a meticulous inspection and reconditioning process. As an Automotive Detailer, you&#39;ll play a critical role in ensuring every vehicle looks its absolute best before it reaches its next owner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lead Automotive Detailer is responsible for both hands-on vehicle detailing and leading the daily detailing operation. This position serves as the subject matter expert for vehicle appearance and cosmetic quality while coordinating a team of detailers to support Ever&#39;s reconditioning process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is an experienced automotive detailer with leadership capabilities who enjoys building efficient processes, maintaining high quality standards, mentoring teammates, and ensuring vehicles are consistently prepared for retail sale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership &amp;amp; Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the daily activities of the detailing team while maintaining a positive and collaborative work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and manage weekly schedules to ensure detailing coverage seven days per week.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate workload and prioritize vehicles based on production deadlines and business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish, document, and continuously improve Ever&#39;s detailing processes and standard operating procedures (SOPs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define cosmetic quality standards to ensure every vehicle meets Ever&#39;s retail-ready expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality inspections before vehicles move to photography, merchandising, or customer delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach and mentor detailing team members on proper techniques, efficiency, and quality expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Recon, Operations, Logistics, and Sales teams to ensure vehicles are completed on schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track detailing productivity and identify opportunities to improve turnaround time and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Inventory &amp;amp; Equipment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage inventory of detailing chemicals, tools, consumables, and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select, evaluate, and purchase detailing supplies while balancing quality, cost, and operational needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain detailing equipment and coordinate repairs or replacement when necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure chemicals and equipment are stored and handled safely in accordance with company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vehicle Detailing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform complete interior and exterior detailing to showroom standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wash, clay bar, polish, wax, and apply protective coatings when required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vacuum, shampoo carpets, clean upholstery, condition leather, and sanitize interiors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remove stains, water spots, adhesive residue, and other cosmetic imperfections.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate buffers, polishers, extractors, steam cleaners, pressure washers, and other detailing equipment safely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify cosmetic issues requiring additional repair or paint correction and communicate findings to the recon team.&l

