&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;Role: Lead Technician&lt;br&gt;Location: Irvine, CA (Onsite)&lt;br&gt;Employment Type: Full-Time&lt;br&gt;Salary: $55-$60 per Hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ever&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ever is building the future of auto retail. As the first AI-native auto retail platform, we are building the next $100B+ automotive business, starting with electric vehicles. Our AI-native product and operations power our full-stack auto retail business, serving EV buyers and sellers across the nation, both online and offline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Based out of San Francisco and expanding nationwide, we are backed by leading investors and led by former tech &amp;amp; automotive professionals from Uber, Tesla, Rivian, Lithia, Penske, Carvana, Lyft, Meta, J.P. Morgan, BCG, and more. After our recently completed Series A financing, we have raised $100M in total equity and debt funding. We are growing rapidly and actively recruiting exceptional talent to join our mission of building the next-generation auto retail platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Lead Technician, you&#39;ll serve as the technical leader of Ever&#39;s reconditioning operation. This role combines advanced hands-on vehicle repair with leadership responsibilities, helping establish best-in-class shop standards while coaching technicians and improving operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll spend a significant portion of your time performing complex repairs and diagnostics while also developing standard operating procedures (SOPs), training technicians, improving quality, and partnering with the Reconditioning Manager to maximize shop throughput, safety, and customer satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What You&#39;ll Own&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform advanced diagnostics, repairs, and vehicle reconditioning on electric and conventional vehicles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the technical escalation point for complex mechanical and electrical repairs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach, mentor, and train technicians on repair quality, efficiency, safety, and OEM best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, document, and continuously improve shop SOPs, repair workflows, quality standards, and inspection processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct quality control inspections before vehicles are released for sale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize repair procedures across the shop to improve consistency and reduce rework&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technician onboarding and hands-on skills development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with workload planning and daily shop prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Reconditioning Manager on productivity initiatives and continuous improvement projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify process bottlenecks and recommend operational improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure technicians follow OEM repair procedures and Ever quality standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation of lean shop practices, 5S organization, and workplace safety initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor repair quality, comeback rates, and technician performance trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with tooling recommendations and shop equipment improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document repairs accurately in Ever systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain compliance with high-voltage safety procedures and OSHA standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a positive, collaborative, and high-performing shop culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Fit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of automotive technician experience with demonstrated technical expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous Lead Technician, Shop Foreman, Team Lead, or similar leadership experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience training, coaching, or mentoring technicians&lt;/li&g

